  "description": {
    "en": "The silky anteater is the smallest anteater in the world, living entirely in trees and resembling a tiny, golden powder puff.",
    "zh": "侏食蚁兽是世界上最小的食蚁兽，完全在树上生活，看起来就像一个微小的金黄色粉扑。"
  },
  "encyclopedia": {
    "anatomy": {
      "en": "They weigh less than a pound! Silky anteaters are covered in soft, golden-yellow fur that helps them blend in with seed pods in the canopy. Their prehensile tail and sharp claws make them expert climbers.",
      "zh": "它们的体重不到半斤！侏食蚁兽浑身覆盖着柔软的金黄色皮毛，这有助于它们伪装成树冠层中的种子荚。它们那能缠绕的尾巴和极其锋利的爪子使它们成为了攀爬大师。"
    },
    "ecology_and_behavior": {
      "en": "These tiny creatures are strictly nocturnal and feed almost entirely on ants—eating up to 8,000 ants a day! When threatened, a silky anteater will stand on its hind legs and raise its claws to look menacing.",
      "zh": "这些微小的生物是严格夜行性的，几乎只吃蚂蚁——每天能吃掉多达 8000 只蚂蚁！当受到威胁时，侏食蚁兽会用后腿站立并高举爪子，摆出一副吓人的防御姿态。"
    },
    "habitat_and_distribution": {
      "en": "Silky anteaters live high up in the canopy of tropical rainforests and mangrove forests across Central and South America. They rarely, if ever, come down to the ground.",
      "zh": "侏食蚁兽生活在中美洲和南美洲热带雨林和红树林极高的树冠层中。它们极少降落到地面上。"
    }
  },
